Use MSTest's `[DataTestMethod]` with `[DataRow]` to parameterize. Each new case becomes a single attribute line instead of a whole method:

```csharp
using Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;

namespace Validation.Tests;

[TestClass]
public sealed class InputValidatorTests
{
    private readonly InputValidator _validator = new();

    [DataTestMethod]
    [DataRow(null, "Input cannot be empty")]
    [DataRow("", "Input cannot be empty")]
    [DataRow("   ", "Input cannot be empty")]
    [DataRow("ab", "Input must be at least 3 characters")]
    [DataRow("hello<script>", "Input contains invalid characters")]
    // Adding a new invalid case? Just add another [DataRow] here.
    public void Validate_InvalidInput_ReturnsFalse(string? input, string expectedError)
    {
        var result = _validator.Validate(input);
        Assert.IsFalse(result.IsValid);
        Assert.AreEqual(expectedError, result.ErrorMessage);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void Validate_TooLong_ReturnsFalse()
    {
        var result = _validator.Validate(new string('x', 256));
        Assert.IsFalse(result.IsValid);
        Assert.AreEqual("Input must not exceed 255 characters", result.ErrorMessage);
    }

    [DataTestMethod]
    [DataRow("hello-world")]
    [DataRow("abc")]
    public void Validate_ValidInput_ReturnsTrue(string input)
    {
        var result = _validator.Validate(input);
        Assert.IsTrue(result.IsValid);
        Assert.IsNull(result.ErrorMessage);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void Validate_MaxLength_ReturnsTrue()
    {
        var result = _validator.Validate(new string('a', 255));
        Assert.IsTrue(result.IsValid);
        Assert.IsNull(result.ErrorMessage);
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**

- **`[DataTestMethod]` + `[DataRow]`** — groups cases that share the same assert logic. New cases = one new attribute line.
- **Two standalone `[TestMethod]`s remain** for generated strings (`new string(...)`) since `[DataRow]` only accepts compile-time constants.
- **Shared `_validator` field** — eliminates repeated construction. MSTest creates a fresh instance per test class run.

To add a new invalid-input case, you'd just write:
```csharp
[DataRow("bad!input", "Input contains invalid characters")]
```

No new method needed.
